    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Football as played under Association rules, where two teams of 11 players each may use any part of their bodies except their hands and arms to maneuver a round ball into the opposing team's goal. Only the goalkeeper is permitted to handle the ball and may do so only within the penalty area surrounding the goal.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
